comments.body:
ee9a74d a couple of ideas

- make the double-to-long conversion explicit
```suggestion
    // Be explicit that we're converting from double to long (CAmount) here.
    // We've previously had bugs creep in from silent double->int conversion.
    CAmount nFee{static_cast<CAmount>(std::ceil(nSatoshisPerK * nSize / 1000.0))};
```
-----

- bypass this calculation in the frequent `GetFeePerK()` case

```cpp
    CAmount nFee{static_cast<CAmount>(
            nSize == 1000 ? nSatoshisPerK : std::ceil(nSatoshisPerK * nSize / 1000.0))};
```

